obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE MULTIMODAL TRANSPORTATION OF GOODSACT, 1993`
  line `ACT NO. 28 OF 1993`
  line `[2 nd April, 1993.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the regulation of the multimodal transportation of goods, from any place in India to`
  line `a place outside India, on the basis of a multimodal transport contract and for matters connected`
  line `therewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `BE it enacted by Parliament in the Forty-fourth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line PRELIMINARY
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.— ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Multimodal`
  line `Transportation of Goods Act, 1993.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 16th day of October, 1992.`
  line `2. Definitions.— In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `1 [( a ) “carrier” means a person who performs or undertakes to perform for hire, the carriage or`
  line `part thereof, of goods by road, rail, inland waterways, sea or air;]`
  line `( b ) “competent authority” means any person or authority authorised by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, to perform the functions of the competent`
  line `authority under this Act;`
  line `( c ) “consignee” means the person named as consignee in the multimodal transport contract;`
  line `( d ) “consignment” means the goods entrusted to a multimodal transport operator for`
  line `multimodal transportation;`
  line `( e ) “consignor” means the person, named in the multimodal transport contract as consignor, by`
  line `whom or on whose behalf the goods covered by such contract are entrusted to a multimodal`
  line `transport operator for multimodal transportation;`
  line `( f ) “delivery” means, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of a negotiable multimodal transport document, delivering of the`
  line `consignment to, or placing the consignment at the disposal of, the consignee or any other`
  line `person entitled to receive it;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a non-negotiable multimodal transport document, delivering of the`
  line `consignment to, or placing the consignment at the disposal of, the consignee or any person`
  line `authorised by the consignee to accept delivery of the consignment on his behalf;`
  line `( g ) “endorsee” means the person in whose favour an endorsement is made, and in the case of`
  line `successive endorsements, the person in whose favour the last endorsement is made;`
  line `( h ) “endorsement” means the signing by the consignee or the endorsee after adding a direction`
  line `on a negotiable multimodal transport document to pass the property in the goods mentioned in such`
  line `document to a specified person;`
  line `2 [( i ) “goods” means any property including live animals, containers, pallets or such other`
  line `articles of transport or packaging supplied by the consignor, irrespective of whether such property`
  line `is to be or is carried on or under the deck;]`
  line `( j ) “mode of transport” means carriage of goods by 3 [road, air, rail] inland waterways or sea;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s.2, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f 5-12-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by s.2, ibid., for clause ( i ) (w.e.f 5-12-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “road, rail” (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of`
  line Ladakh.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `1 [( k ) “multimodal transportation” means carriage of goods, by at least two different modes of`
  line `transport under a multimodal transport contract, from the place of acceptance of the goods in India`
  line `to a place of delivery of the goods outside India;`
  line `( l ) “multimodal transport contract” means a contract under which a multimodal transport`
  line `operator undertakes to perform or procure the performance of multimodal transportation against`
  line `payment of freight;`
  line `( la ) “multimodal transport document” means a negotiable or non-negotiable document`
  line `evidencing a multimodal transport contract and which can be replaced by electronic data`
  line `interchange messages permitted by applicable law;]`
  line `( m ) “multimodal transport operator” means any person who—`
  line `( i ) concludes a multimodal transport contract on his own behalf or through another`
  line `person acting on his behalf;`
  line `( ii ) acts as principal, and 2 [not as an agent either of the consignor, or consignee or of the`
  line `carrier] participating in the multimodal transportation, and who assumes responsibility for the`
  line `performance of the said contract; and`
  line `( iii ) is registered under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 4;`
  line `( n ) “negotiable multimodal transport document” means a multimodal transport document which`
  line `is —`
  line `( i ) made out to order or to bearer; or`
  line `( ii ) made out to order and is transferable by endorsement; or`
  line `( iii ) made out to bearer and is transferable without endorsement;`
  line `( o ) “non-negotiable multimodal transport document” means a multimodal transport document`
  line `which indicates only one named consignee;`
  line `( p ) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( q ) “registration” means registration of multimodal transport operator under sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line `3 [( r ) “special drawing rights” means such units of accounts as are determined by the`
  line `International Monetary Fund;`
  line `( s ) “taking charge” means that the goods have been handed over to and accepted for carriage by`
  line `the multimodal transport operator.]`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `R EGULATION OF MULTIMODAL TRANSPORTATION`
  line `3. No person to carry on business without registration. —No person shall carry on or commence`
  line `the business of multimodal transportation unless he is registered under this Act:`
  line `Provided that a person carrying on the business of multimodal transportation immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, may continue to do so for a period of three months from such`
  line `commencement; and if he has made an application for registration within the said period, till the disposal`
  line `of such application.`
  line `4. Registration for multimodal transportation. —( 1 ) Any person may apply for registration to the`
  line `competent authority to carry on or commence the business of multimodal transportation.`
  line `( 2 ) An application under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a fee of ten thousand rupees.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 2, for clauses ( k ) and ( l ) (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “not as an agent either of the consignor or of the carrier”(w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( 3 ) On receipt of the application, the competent authority shall satisfy that the applicant fulfils the`
  line `following conditions, namely:—`
  line `1 [( a ) ( i ) that the applicant is a company, firm or proprietary concern, engaged either in the`
  line `business of shipping, or freight forwarding in India or abroad with a minimum annual turnover of`
  line `fifty lakh rupees during the immediately preceding financial year or an average annual turnover of`
  line `fifty lakh rupees during the preceding three financial years as certified by a Chartered Accountant`
  line `within the meaning of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949 );`
  line `( ii ) that if the applicant is a company, firm or proprietary concern other than a company, firm or`
  line `proprietary concern, specified in sub-clause ( i ), the subscribed share capital of such company or the`
  line `aggregate balance in the capital account of partners of the firm, or the capital of the proprietor is not`
  line `less than fifty lakh rupees;]`
  line `( b ) that the applicant has offices or agents or representatives in not less than two other countries,`
  line `and on being so satisfied, register the applicant as a multimodal transport operator and grant a certificate`
  line `to it to carry on or commence the business of multimodal transportation:`
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, refuse to grant`
  line `registration if it is satisfied that the applicant does not fulfil the said conditions:`
  line `2 [Provided further that any applicant who is not a resident of India and who is not engaged in the`
  line `business of shipping shall not be granted registration unless he has established a place of business in`
  line `India:`
  line `Provided also that in respect of any applicant who is not a resident of India, the turnover may be`
  line `certified by any authority competent to certify the accounts of a company in that country.]`
  line `3 [( 4 ) A certificate granted under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be valid for a period of three years and may be`
  line `renewed from time to time for a further period of three years at a time.`
  line `( 5 ) An application for renewal shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by such amount of fees as may be notified by the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that such fees shall not be less than rupees ten thousand and shall not exceed rupees twenty`
  line thousand.
  line `( 6 ) The competent authority shall renew the registration certificate granted under sub-section ( 3 ) if`
  line `the applicant continues to fulfil the conditions as laid down at the time of registration.]`
  line `5. Cancellation of registration. — The competent authority may, if it is satisfied at any time after`
  line `registration that —`
  line `( a ) any statement in, or in relation to, any application under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 4 or its`
  line `renewal under sub-section ( 5 ) of that section, is incorrect or false in any material particular; or`
  line `( b ) any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder has been contravened by the`
  line `multimodal transport operator; or`
  line `( c ) the multimodal transport operator has not entered into any multimodal transport contract`
  line `during the preceding two years after his registration,`
  line `cancel by order the certificate of registration:`
  line `Provided that no such registration shall be cancelled unless the multimodal transport operator has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed action.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 3, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 5-12-2000 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `6. Appeal.— 1 [( 1 ) Any person aggrieved by, refusal of the competent authority to grant or renew`
  line `registration under section 4 or by cancellation of registration under section 5, may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `Central Government within such period as may be prescribed.]`
  line `( 2 ) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the prescribed period:`
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the prescribed period if the appellant`
  line `satisfies the Central Government that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the`
  line `prescribed period.`
  line `( 3 ) Every appeal made under this section shall be made in such form and on payment of such fees as`
  line `may be prescribed and shall be accompanied by a copy of the order appealed against.`
  line `( 4 ) On receipt of any such appeal, the Central Government shall, after giving the parties a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard and after making such inquiry as it deems proper, make such order as it thinks`
  line fit.
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `M ULTIMODAL TRANSPORT DOCUMENT`
  line `7. Issue of multimodal transport document. — ( 1 ) Where the consignor and the multimodal`
  line `transport operator have entered into a contract for the multimodal transportation and the multimodal`
  line `transport operator has taken charge of the goods, he shall, at the option of the consignor, issue a`
  line `negotiable or non-negotiable multimodal transport document:`
  line `2 [Provided that the multimodal transport operator shall issue the multimodal transport document only`
  line `after obtaining, and during the subsistence of a valid insurance cover.]`
  line `( 2 ) The multimodal transport document shall be signed by the multimodal transport operator or by a`
  line `person duly authorised by him.`
  line `8. Multimodal transport document to be regarded as document of title. — ( 1 ) Every consignee`
  line `named in the negotiable or non-negotiable multimodal transport document and every endorsee of such`
  line `document, as the case may be, to whom the property in the goods mentioned therein shall pass, upon or`
  line `by reason of such consignment or endorsement, shall have all the rights and liabilities of the consignor.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall prejudice or affect the right of the multimodal transport`
  line `operator to claim freight from the consignor or enforce any liability of the consignee or endorsee by`
  line `reason of his being such consignee or endorsee.`
  line `9. Contents of multimodal transport document.— The multimodal transport document shall contain`
  line `the following particulars, namely: —`
  line `3 [( a ) the general nature of the goods, the leading marks necessary for identification of the goods,`
  line `the character of the goods (including dangerous goods), the number of packages or units and the gross`
  line `weight and quantity of the goods as declared by the consignor;]`
  line `( b ) apparent condition of the goods;`
  line `( c ) the name and principal place of business of the multimodal transport operator;`
  line `( d ) the name of the consignor;`
  line `( e ) the name of the consignee, if specified by the consignor;`
  line `( f ) the place and date of taking charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator;`
  line `( g ) theplace of delivery of the goods;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 4, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f 5-12-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `1 [( h ) the date or the period of delivery of the goods by the multimodal transport operator as`
  line `expressly agreed upon between the consignor and the multimodal transport operator;]`
  line `( i ) whether it is negotiable or non-negotiable;`
  line `( j ) the place and date of its issue;`
  line `2 [( k ) freight payable by the consignor or the consignee, as the case may be, to be mentioned only`
  line `if expressly agreed by both the consignor and the consignee;]`
  line `( l ) the signature of the multimodal transport operator or of a person duly authorised by him;`
  line `( m ) the intended journey route, modes of transport and places of transhipment, if known at the`
  line `time of its issue;`
  line `( n ) terms of shipment and a statement that the document has been issued subject to and in`
  line `accordance with this Act; and`
  line `( o ) any other particular which the parties may agree to insert in the document, if any such`
  line `particular is not inconsistent with any law for the time being in force:`
  line `3 [Provided that the absence of any of the particulars listed above shall not affect the legal`
  line `character of the multimodal transport document.]`
  line `10. Reservation in the multimodal transport document.— ( 1 ) Where the multimodal transport`
  line `operator or a person acting on his behalf knows, or has reasonable grounds to suspect, that the particulars`
  line `furnished by the consignor in the multimodal transport document do not accurately represent the goods`
  line `actually taken in charge, or if he has no reasonable means of checking such particulars, the multimodal`
  line `transport operator or a person acting on his behalf shall insert in the multimodal transport document a`
  line `reservation specifying the inaccuracies, if any, the grounds of suspicion or the absence of reasonable`
  line `means of checking the particulars.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the multimodal transport operator or a person acting on his behalf fails to insert the`
  line `reservation in the multimodal transport document relating to the apparent condition of the goods, he shall`
  line `be deemed to have accepted the goods in apparent good condition.`
  line `11. Evidentiary effect of the multimodal transport document.— Save as provided in section 10, —`
  line `( a ) the multimodal transport document shall be prima facie evidence of the fact that the`
  line `multimodal transport operator has taken charge of the goods as described in the document;and`
  line `( b ) no proof to the contrary by the multimodal transport operator shall be admissible if the`
  line `multimodal transport document is issued in negotiable form and has been transmitted to the consignee`
  line `or transferred by the consignee to a third party, if the consignee or the third party has acted in good`
  line `faith relying on the description of the goods in the document.`
  line `12. Responsibility of the consignor.— ( 1 ) The consignor shall be deemed to have guaranteed to the`
  line `multimodal transport operator the adequacy and accuracy, at the time the multimodal transport operator`
  line `takes charge of the goods, of the particulars referred to in clauses ( a ) and ( b ) of section 9 as furnished by`
  line `the consignor for insertion in the multimodal transport document.`
  line `( 2 ) The consignor shall indemnify the multimodal transport operator against loss resulting from`
  line `inadequacy or inaccuracy of the particulars referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) The right of the multimodal transport operator under sub-section ( 2 ) shall in no way limit his`
  line `liability under the multimodal transport contract to any person other than the consignor.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `R ESPONSIBILITIES AND LIABILITIES OF THE MULTIMODAL TRANSPORT OPERATOR`
  line `13. Basis of liability of multimodal transport operator.— ( 1 ) The multimodal transport operator`
  line `shall be liable for loss resulting from —`
  line `( a ) any loss of, or damage to, the consignment;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 6, for clause ( h ) (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for clause ( k ) (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f5-12-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `( b ) delay in delivery of the consignment and any consequential loss or damage arising from such`
  line delay,
  line `where such loss, damage or delay in delivery took place while the consignment was in his charge:`
  line `Provided that the multimodal transport operator shall not be liable if he proves that no fault or neglect`
  line `on his part or that of his servants or agents had caused or contributed to such loss, damage or delay in`
  line `delivery:`
  line `1 [Provided further that the multimodal transport operator shall not be liable for loss or damage arising`
  line `out of delay in delivery including any consequential loss or damage arising from such delay unless the`
  line `consignor had made a declaration of interest in timely delivery which has been accepted by the`
  line `multimodal transport operator.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, “delay in delivery” shall be deemed to occur`
  line `when the consignment has not been delivered within the time expressly agreed upon or, in the absence of`
  line `such agreement, within a reasonable time required by a diligent multimodal transport operator, having`
  line `regard to the circumstances of the case, to effect the delivery of the consignment.`
  line `( 2 ) If the consignment has not been delivered within ninety consecutive days following the date of`
  line `delivery expressly agreed upon or the reasonable time referred to in the Explanation to sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `the claimant may treat the consignment as lost.`
  line `14. Limits of liability when the nature and value of the consignment have not been declared and`
  line `stage of transport where loss or damage occurred is not known.— ( 1 ) Where a multimodal transport`
  line `operator becomes liable for any loss of, or damage to, any consignment, the nature and value whereof`
  line `have not been declared by the consignor before such consignment has been taken in charge by the`
  line `multimodal transport operator and the stage of transport at which such loss or damage occurred is not`
  line `known, then the liability of the multimodal transport operator to pay compensation shall not exceed two`
  line `Special Drawing Rights per kilogram of the gross weight of the consignment lost or damaged or 666.67`
  line `Special Drawing Rights per package or unit lost or damaged, whichever is higher.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purpose of this sub-section, where a container, pallet or similar article is`
  line `stuffed with more than one package or units, the packages or units enumerated in the multimodal`
  line `transport document, as packed in such container, pallet or similar article of transport shall be deemed as`
  line `packages or units.]`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), if the multimodal transportation does not,`
  line `according to the multimodal transport contract, include carriage of goods by sea or by inland waterways,`
  line `the liability of the multimodal transport operator shall be limited to an amount not exceeding 8.33 Special`
  line `Drawing Rights per kilogram of the gross weight of the goods lost or damaged.`
  line `15. Limits of liability when the nature and value of the consignment have not been declared and`
  line `stage of transport where loss or damage occurred is known.— Where a multimodal transport operator`
  line `becomes liable for any loss of, or damage to, any consignment, the nature and value whereof have not`
  line `been declared by the consignor before such consignment has been taken in charge by the multimodal`
  line `transport operator and the stage of transport at which such loss or damage occurred is known, then the`
  line `limit of the liability of the multimodal transport operator for such loss or damage shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the relevant law applicable in relation to the mode of transport during`
  line `the course of which the loss or damage occurred and any stipulation in the multimodal transport contract`
  line `to the contrary shall be void and unenforceable:`
  line `3 [Provided that the multimodal transport operator shall not be liable for any loss, damage or delay in`
  line `delivery due to a cause for which the carrier is exempted from liability in accordance with the applicable`
  line law.]
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2000, s. 7, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid.,forthe Explanation (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `16. Liability of the multimodal transport operator in case of delay in delivery of goods under`
  line `certain circumstances. — Where delay in delivery of the consignment occurs under any of the`
  line `circumstances mentioned in the Explanation to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13, or any consequential loss or`
  line `damage arises from such delay, then the liability of the multimodal transport operator shall be limited to`
  line `the freight payable for the consignment so delayed.`
  line `17. Assessment of compensation.— ( 1 ) Assessment of compensation for loss of, or damage to, the`
  line `consignment shall be made with reference to the value of such consignment at the place where, and the`
  line `time at which, such consignment is delivered to the consignee or at the place and time when, in`
  line `accordance with the multimodal transport contract, it should have been delivered.`
  line `( 2 ) The value of the consignment shall be determined according to the current commodity exchange`
  line `price, or, if there is no such price, according to the current market price, or, if the current market price is`
  line `not ascertainable, with reference to the normal value of a consignment of the same kind and quantity.`
  line `18. Loss of right of multimodal transport operator to limit liability. — The multimodal transport`
  line `operator shall not be entitled to the benefit of limitation of liability under any of the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter if it is proved that the loss, damage or delay in delivery of consignment resulted from an act or`
  line `omission of the multimodal transport operator with intent to cause such loss, damage or delay or`
  line `recklessly and with knowledge that such loss, damage or delay would probably result.`
  line `19. Limit of liability of multimodal transport operator for total loss of goods.— The multimodal`
  line `transport operator shall not, in any case, be liable for an amount greater than the liability for total loss of`
  line `goods for which a person will be entitled to make a claim against him under the provisions of this Act.`
  line `20. Notice of loss of or damage to goods.— ( 1 ) The delivery of the consignment to the consignee by`
  line `the multimodal transport operator shall be treated as prima facie evidence of delivery of the goods as`
  line `described in the multimodal transport document unless notice of the general nature of loss of, or damage`
  line `to, the goods is given, in writing, by the consignee to the multimodal transport operator at the time of`
  line `handing over of the goods to the consignee.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the loss or damage is not apparent, the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply unless`
  line `notice in writing is given by the consignee of the loss of, or damage to, the goods within six consecutive`
  line `days after the day when the goods were handed over to the consignee.`
  line `1 [ 20A. Period of responsibility. — The responsibility of the multimodal transport operator for the`
  line `goods under this Act shall cover the period from the time he has taken the goods in his charge to the time`
  line `of their delivery.]`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `21. Special provision for dangerous goods. — ( 1 ) Where the consignor hands over the prescribed`
  line `dangerous goods to a multimodal transport operator or any person acting on behalf of such operator, the`
  line `consignor shall inform him of the nature of the dangerous goods and, if necessary, the precautions to be`
  line `taken while transporting such goods.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the consignor fails to inform the multimodal transport operator or the other person acting`
  line `on behalf of such operator of the nature of the dangerous goods and such operator or person does not`
  line `otherwise have knowledge of the dangerous goods —`
  line `( a ) the consignor shall be liable to the multimodal transport operator or the other person acting on`
  line `behalf of such operator for all loss resulting from the multimodal transportation of such goods; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2000,s. 10(w.e.f. 5-12-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `( b ) the goods may at any time be unloaded, destroyed or rendered innocuous, as the`
  line `circumstances may require, without payment of compensation.`
  line `22. Right of multimodal transport operator to have lien on goods and documents. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `multimodal transport operator who has not been paid the amount of consideration stipulated in the`
  line `multimodal transport contract shall have a lien on the consignment and on the documents in his`
  line possession.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 13, 16 and 18, the period during which the goods`
  line `are in possession of the multimodal transport operator in exercise of his right of lien referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) shall not be included for the purposes of calculating the time of delay under any of those`
  line sections.
  line `23. General average.—Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, it`
  line `shall be lawful for the parties to the multimodal transport contract to include in the multimodal transport`
  line `document any provision relating to general average.`
  line `Explanation.— For the purposes of this section, “general average” means loss, damage or expense`
  line `reasonably incurred in order to avert danger to property in common peril and in the common interest`
  line `involved in the multimodal transportation.`
  line `24. Limitation on action. — The multimodal transport operator shall not be liable under any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act unless action against him is brought within nine months of —`
  line `( a ) the date of delivery of the goods, or`
  line `( b ) the date when the goods should have been delivered, or`
  line `( c ) the date on and from which the party entitled to receive delivery of the goods has the right to`
  line `treat the goods as lost under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 13.`
  line `25. Jurisdiction for instituting action. — Any party to the multimodal transport contract may institute`
  line `an action in a court which is competent and within the jurisdiction of which is situated one of the`
  line `following places, namely:—`
  line `( a ) the principal place of business, or, in the absence thereof, the habitual residence, of the`
  line `defendant; or`
  line `( b ) the place where the multimodal transport contract was made, provided that the defendant has a`
  line `place of business, branch or agency at such place; or`
  line `( c ) the place of taking charge of the goods for multimodal transportation or the place of delivery`
  line `thereof; or`
  line `( d ) any other place specified in the multimodal transport contract and evidenced in the`
  line `multimodal transport document.`
  line `26. Arbitration. — ( 1 ) The parties to a multimodal transport contract may provide therein that any`
  line `dispute which may arise in relation to multimodal transportation under the provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `referred to arbitration.`
  line `( 2 ) The arbitration proceeding may be instituted at such place or in accordance with such procedure`
  line `as may be specified in the multimodal transport document.`
  line `27. Delegation of power. — The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act, except the power under section 30, shall, in such`
  line `circumstances and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified therein, be exercisable also by`
  line `such officer or authority as may be specified in the notification.`
  line `28. Multimodal transport contract to be made in accordance with this Act. — No person`
  line `registered as a multimodal transport operator shall enter into any contract for multimodal transportation`
  line `except in accordance with the provisions of this Act and any contract, to the extent it is inconsistent with`
  line `the said provisions, shall be void and unenforceable.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `29. Act to override other enactments. — The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
  line `30. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the forms in which applications shall be made under section 4;`
  line `( b ) the period within which appeal shall be preferred under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 6;`
  line `( c ) the form in which an appeal shall be preferred under section 6 and the amount of fee payable`
  line `in respect of such appeal;`
  line `( d ) dangerous goods for the purpose of section 21;`
  line `( e ) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
  line `31. [ Amendment of certain enactments ]. —Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 2001`
  line `(30 of 2001), s. 2 and the First Schedul e ( w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
  line `32. Repeal and savings. — ( 1 ) The Multimodal Transportation of Goods Ordinance,`
  line `1993 (Ord. 6 of1993) is hereby repealed.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line `[ THE SCHEDULE ] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001), s. 2 and the First`
  line `Schedule ( w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
